<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>GNN-NIDS Analysis Report</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif; margin: 40px; color: #111; font-size: 13px; }
  h1 { font-size: 22px; color: #1e3a5f; border-bottom: 2px solid #1e3a5f; padding-bottom: 8px; }
  h2 { font-size: 16px; color: #1e3a5f; margin-top: 28px; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px; font-size: 12px; }
  th { background: #1e3a5f; color: #fff; padding: 6px 10px; text-align: left; }
  td { padding: 5px 10px; border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb; }
  tr:hover td { background: #f9fafb; }
  .meta-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 12px; margin: 16px 0; }
  .meta-card { background: #f3f4f6; border-radius: 6px; padding: 12px; }
  .meta-card .label { font-size: 11px; color: #6b7280; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .meta-card .value { font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #1e3a5f; margin-top: 4px; }
  .badge { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 9999px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; }
  .badge-attack { background: #fee2e2; color: #b91c1c; }
  .badge-benign { background: #d1fae5; color: #065f46; }
  .graph-img { max-width: 100%; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 6px; margin-top: 10px; }
  .reliability-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; }
  .model-card { background: #f3f4f6; border-radius: 6px; padding: 14px; }
  .metric-row { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; margin: 6px 0; }
  .metric-label { color: #6b7280; }
  .metric-value { font-weight: bold; }
  @media print { body { margin: 20px; } }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>GNN-NIDS Analysis Report</h1>
<p style="color:#6b7280">Session: {{ session_id }} &nbsp;|&nbsp; Generated: {{ generated_at }}</p>

<h2>1. Summary</h2>
<div class="meta-grid">
  <div class="meta-card"><div class="label">Total Flows</div><div class="value">{{ total_flows }}</div></div>
  <div class="meta-card"><div class="label">Alerts Raised</div><div class="value">{{ total_alerts }}</div></div>
  <div class="meta-card"><div class="label">Time Windows</div><div class="value">{{ n_windows }}</div></div>
</div>
<p><strong>File:</strong> {{ filename }}</p>

<h2>2. Top Alerts (by Confidence)</h2>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Flow ID</th><th>Src → Dst</th><th>Attack Type</th><th>Confidence</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for a in top_alerts %}
  <tr>
    <td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
    <td>{{ a.flow_id }}</td>
    <td>{{ a.src }} → {{ a.dst }}</td>
    <td><span class="badge badge-attack">{{ a.attack_type }}</span></td>
    <td>{{ "%.1f"|format(a.confidence * 100) }}%</td>
  </tr>
  {% else %}
  <tr><td colspan="5" style="color:#9ca3af;text-align:center">No alerts detected</td></tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>

{% if graph_png_b64 %}
<h2>3. Traffic Graph Snapshot</h2>
<img class="graph-img" src="data:image/png;base64,{{ graph_png_b64 }}" alt="Traffic Graph">
{% endif %}

<h2>4. Model Reliability</h2>
<div class="reliability-grid">
{% for model_name, metrics in reliability.items() %}
<div class="model-card">
  <strong style="text-transform:capitalize">{{ model_name }}</strong>
  <div class="metric-row"><span class="metric-label">Clean F1</span>
    <span class="metric-value">{% if metrics.clean_f1 %}{{ "%.3f"|format(metrics.clean_f1) }}{% else %}TBD{% endif %}</span></div>
  <div class="metric-row"><span class="metric-label">DR under C-PGD (ε=0.1)</span>
    <span class="metric-value">{% if metrics.dr_under_cpgd_eps01 %}{{ "%.3f"|format(metrics.dr_under_cpgd_eps01) }}{% else %}TBD{% endif %}</span></div>
  <div class="metric-row"><span class="metric-label">ΔF1 after adv. training</span>
    <span class="metric-value">{% if metrics.delta_f1_after_adv_training %}+{{ "%.3f"|format(metrics.delta_f1_after_adv_training) }}{% else %}TBD{% endif %}</span></div>
</div>
{% else %}
<p style="color:#9ca3af">Reliability metrics not yet computed. Run <code>scripts/compute_reliability_metrics.py</code>.</p>
{% endfor %}
</div>

<h2>5. Methodology</h2>
<p>
  This report was generated by <strong>GNN-NIDS Analyzer</strong> using a Graph Neural Network trained on NF-UNSW-NB15-v2.
  Network flows are grouped into 60-second windows and represented as a directed graph (nodes = IP:Port endpoints, edges = flows).
  The GNN classifies each edge as benign or one of 9 attack categories using weighted cross-entropy to handle class imbalance.
  Adversarial examples are generated with Constrained PGD (C-PGD, ε={{ "0.10" }}, 40 steps) enforcing TCP validity, feature co-dependency, and empirical bounds (CSR = 1.0).
</p>

</body>
</html>
